# Skills Library — use it to do better work

A local clone of the open-source skills library lives at:

`~/claude-skills-library/free-skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`

(Source: github.com/frankxai/claude-skills-library — MIT. Update with
`git -C ~/claude-skills-library pull`.)

## When to use
Before doing specialized work, check whether a matching skill exists and READ its
`SKILL.md` (and `references/` if present) to follow current best practices.
Treat the skill as authoritative guidance for that domain.

## High-value skills for our stack
| Task | Skill |
|------|-------|
| Next.js / web app work | `nextjs-expert` |
| UI / UX / accessibility | `ui-ux-design-expert` |
| Product specs (the 6 kickoff docs) | `product-management-expert` |
| Reviewing a diff / PR | `github-code-review` |
| Designing an MCP server | `mcp-architecture`, `mcp-builder` |
| Perf / profiling | `performance-analysis` |
| Verification / quality gates | `verification-quality` |
| Docs output (docx/pptx/xlsx/pdf) | `anthropic/docx`, `anthropic/pptx`, etc. |

Browse all: `ls ~/claude-skills-library/free-skills`

## How to apply
1. Identify the task domain.
2. `ls ~/claude-skills-library/free-skills` (or check the table above) for a match.
3. Read that `SKILL.md`, then follow it while completing the task.
4. If nothing matches, proceed normally.
